WEBVTT

00:03.873 --> 00:05.309
Previously...

00:05.440 --> 00:07.026
- You need more men.
- I'll leave tomorrow.

00:07.050 --> 00:08.462
I will promise to stand
by your side,

00:08.486 --> 00:09.792
Colonel Fraser, sir.

00:09.922 --> 00:11.552
Confirmed sightings
of Bonnet in Wilmington.

00:11.576 --> 00:12.838
Bree doesn't know, does she?

00:12.969 --> 00:14.449
No.

00:14.536 --> 00:16.842
Kezzie and I
are indentured to a man

00:16.973 --> 00:18.453
who lives not far from here.

00:18.583 --> 00:19.865
Take these lads
and the rest of the company

00:19.889 --> 00:21.499
and continue to Brownsville.

00:21.630 --> 00:24.676
Claire and I will go see
this Mr. Beardsley.

00:24.807 --> 00:25.914
I must speak with your husband.

00:25.938 --> 00:26.938
Husband's dead.

00:26.983 --> 00:27.983
I would like to purchase

00:28.028 --> 00:29.290
yer two bond servants.

00:29.420 --> 00:30.682
Keep 'em.
I got no use for 'em.

00:32.380 --> 00:34.077
You said he was dead.

00:34.164 --> 00:36.514
He struck me, and then he fell,
and I couldn't move him.

00:38.081 --> 00:40.083
Baby's father is black.

00:40.214 --> 00:42.390
You hear that?
She isn't yours.

00:42.477 --> 00:45.045
- Fanny?
- She's not coming back.

00:45.175 --> 00:46.370
She left the deed with the baby.

00:46.394 --> 00:47.394
And indenture papers.

00:49.179 --> 00:51.355
♪ Sing me a song ♪

00:51.442 --> 00:54.619
♪ Of a lass that is gone ♪

00:54.793 --> 00:56.665
♪ Say, could that lass ♪

00:56.839 --> 01:00.147
♪ Be I? ♪

01:00.234 --> 01:02.149
♪ Merry of soul ♪

01:02.323 --> 01:05.239
♪ She sailed on a day ♪

01:05.413 --> 01:07.154
♪ Over the sea ♪

01:07.328 --> 01:10.461
♪ To Skye ♪

01:10.635 --> 01:13.160
♪ Billow and breeze ♪

01:13.334 --> 01:15.771
♪ Islands and seas ♪

01:15.858 --> 01:18.730
♪ Mountains of rain and sun ♪

01:18.817 --> 01:21.081
♪ Mountains of rain
and sun ♪

01:21.255 --> 01:23.431
♪ All that was good ♪

01:23.605 --> 01:26.086
♪ All that was fair ♪

01:26.260 --> 01:28.218
♪ All that was me ♪

01:28.392 --> 01:31.265
♪ Is gone ♪

01:31.439 --> 01:33.745
♪ Sing me a song ♪

01:33.832 --> 01:36.444
♪ Of a lass that is gone ♪

01:36.618 --> 01:38.576
♪ Say, could that lass ♪

01:38.750 --> 01:41.884
♪ Be I? ♪

01:41.971 --> 01:43.842
♪ Merry of soul ♪

01:44.016 --> 01:46.932
♪ She sailed on a day ♪

01:47.107 --> 01:50.849
♪ Over the sea ♪

01:51.023 --> 01:56.725
♪ To Skye ♪

02:00.642 --> 02:02.774
♪

02:02.948 --> 02:06.996
♪ Sing me a song ♪

02:07.170 --> 02:09.346
♪ Of a lass ♪

02:09.433 --> 02:12.697
♪ That is gone ♪

02:12.784 --> 02:17.441
♪ Say, could that lass ♪

02:17.615 --> 02:21.445
♪ Be I? ♪♪♪

02:21.619 --> 02:24.405
♪

02:53.434 --> 02:54.870
Halloo the house!

02:56.088 --> 02:57.088
Attendez.

02:59.570 --> 03:00.789
Do not move.

03:03.487 --> 03:05.924
I'm Captain Roger MacKenzie,

03:06.055 --> 03:07.665
in command of a militia
serving under

03:07.796 --> 03:10.973
Colonel James Fraser
of Fraser's Ridge.

03:11.103 --> 03:13.193
We saw you up the road,
Morton, you bastard.

03:18.198 --> 03:19.808
You'll pay for what you did!

03:19.982 --> 03:21.679
♪

03:36.694 --> 03:38.392
What do you want with Morton?

03:38.522 --> 03:40.002
None of your concern.

03:40.132 --> 03:41.132
Hand him over.

03:44.963 --> 03:46.704
Do you think they're Regulators?

03:46.791 --> 03:48.073
Well, not unless Morton's
secretly a corrupt

03:48.097 --> 03:49.968
tax collector in disguise.

03:50.099 --> 03:51.274
Isaiah!

03:51.405 --> 03:54.364
I'm sorry.
I had to tell.

03:54.495 --> 03:57.193
I couldn't marry Elijah Ford.

03:57.280 --> 03:59.848
Please, Isaiah,
say you'll do right by me.

04:00.022 --> 04:02.329
♪

04:02.459 --> 04:04.287
- Don't hurt him!
- Alicia!

04:04.418 --> 04:05.984
I'd rather die
than be without him!

04:06.115 --> 04:07.551
Have a shred of dignity.

04:09.161 --> 04:11.555
Shouting for all the world
to hear of your shame.

04:11.642 --> 04:13.209
Isaiah.

04:14.863 --> 04:16.212
What can we do?
What can we do?

04:17.735 --> 04:19.215
Oh, Lord, give me courage.

04:25.134 --> 04:26.831
I suppose we better do
as they ask.

04:26.962 --> 04:28.442
What?

04:28.572 --> 04:30.139
Turn Morton over to them?

04:30.270 --> 04:31.793
Aye.

04:33.925 --> 04:35.251
We're gonna need some
of that whisky, Fergus.

04:35.275 --> 04:37.668
Oh, are you sure?

04:37.799 --> 04:40.323
Oh.

04:40.454 --> 04:43.413
Aye, and get a full bottle,
please.

04:44.849 --> 04:46.460
A bit of Dutch courage
is all we need.

04:46.590 --> 04:48.375
Aye, Captain.

04:48.505 --> 04:50.551
Stand down.

04:50.638 --> 04:53.858
Stand down.

04:54.032 --> 04:56.818
♪

05:13.574 --> 05:16.794
♪

05:21.146 --> 05:22.409
How was town, Mistress?

05:22.539 --> 05:24.541
- It was good... and busy.
- Oh.

05:24.672 --> 05:28.110
We got paper and books,
fabrics, linen, cotton.

05:28.240 --> 05:29.851
Oh, canna wait to see them.

05:29.981 --> 05:32.462
And something
a little special for you.

05:32.549 --> 05:33.637
- For me?
- Mm-hmm.

05:33.768 --> 05:35.291
You'll smell
like orange blossom.

05:35.422 --> 05:37.293
Thank you, Mistress.

05:37.380 --> 05:38.947
Now, let's go inside

05:39.034 --> 05:42.516
and, uh, make stew
and dumplings.

05:42.603 --> 05:44.996
What do you think, Mr. Bug?

05:45.127 --> 05:47.042
Go all that way to town
for sugar,

05:47.172 --> 05:48.957
and it's savory dumplings again?

05:49.087 --> 05:50.543
Well, we all know
you're sweet enough.

05:50.567 --> 05:52.395
Ugh, stop your nonsense.

05:52.526 --> 05:56.573
Mrs. Bug...
where did Jemmy get this?

05:56.704 --> 05:58.662
While you were collecting the post,

05:58.793 --> 06:01.839
a man ruffled Jemmy's hair
and gave him a coin.

06:01.970 --> 06:03.145
Did he say anything?

06:03.232 --> 06:05.408
He said, "What a handsome lad,"

06:05.539 --> 06:08.977
and, uh, did he take after
his mother or his father?

06:09.064 --> 06:11.371
And then just gave him a coin?

06:11.501 --> 06:12.546
He say anything else?

06:12.676 --> 06:14.417
He was Irish, you see.

06:14.504 --> 06:17.072
So, of course, once they get
talking about this and that,

06:17.159 --> 06:18.223
it can take all day, but...

06:18.247 --> 06:19.596
What did he look like?

06:19.727 --> 06:23.121
A gentlemen, he was,
fair and strong.

06:23.208 --> 06:25.428
Did he have a scar here?

06:25.515 --> 06:27.952
I'm sorry.
I dinna recall.

06:28.083 --> 06:31.216
I hope you don't think
I would ever let the bairn
come in harm's way.

06:31.347 --> 06:34.089
No, no, I-I know.

06:34.219 --> 06:37.571
I just know all about the Irish
gift of the gab, that's all.

06:37.701 --> 06:40.704
Don't want Jemmy's mind filled
with superstitious nonsense
about luck.

06:42.489 --> 06:43.838
- Let's forget about it.
- Aye.

06:45.492 --> 06:47.363
I'll call you
when the stew's ready.

06:49.452 --> 06:52.237
Here.

06:52.368 --> 06:55.110
Um, with so many away
from the Ridge,

06:55.240 --> 06:57.567
I think maybe we should move
into the big house
with everyone.

06:57.591 --> 06:59.201
Aye, mistress.

06:59.288 --> 07:01.725
It is nice to have company.

07:04.859 --> 07:07.557
♪

07:13.258 --> 07:16.392
Isaiah.

07:19.395 --> 07:22.267
♪

07:28.709 --> 07:31.494
♪

07:37.108 --> 07:39.067
How much for a cask?

07:39.197 --> 07:41.112
We'll buy some,
and you can be on your way.

07:41.243 --> 07:44.072
Will you oblige me
and have a little more?

07:44.159 --> 07:46.291
What are you, whisky merchants?

07:46.422 --> 07:48.468
Heh, no.
No, no.

07:48.598 --> 07:51.209
As I was saying earlier,
we are militiamen

07:51.296 --> 07:54.474
charged by Governor Tryon
to march against
the Regulators.

07:54.604 --> 07:55.910
Hmm.

08:04.396 --> 08:06.181
Well, it's tolerable,
I'll admit.

08:08.488 --> 08:11.882
Then perhaps I can
propose a toast... hmm?

08:12.013 --> 08:13.667
To the men of Brownsville

08:13.797 --> 08:15.317
and to the men
of the Fraser's Company.

08:20.325 --> 08:21.588
Au courage.

08:33.077 --> 08:34.664
We've come to notify you
of your obligation

08:34.688 --> 08:36.428
to provide men.

08:36.516 --> 08:38.518
Heh.
"Obligation"?

08:38.648 --> 08:41.608
Or opportunity, I should say.

08:41.738 --> 08:44.654
40 shillings and two shillings
every day thereafter
for each man.

08:45.786 --> 08:48.223
The only present obligation
I have is to my daughter...

08:50.660 --> 08:52.986
And these men here,
who'll break that boy's neck
without hesitation

08:53.010 --> 08:54.577
if I give the word.

08:54.708 --> 08:56.927
What could a young lad
like Morton possibly have done

08:57.058 --> 08:58.625
that can't be resolved
over a drink?

08:58.755 --> 09:01.453
That bastard's cost me
a fortune.

09:01.584 --> 09:04.152
I had a match arranged
with my daughter.

09:04.282 --> 09:07.285
Elijah Ford brought with him
almost 10 acres

09:07.416 --> 09:08.765
and a decent trade in tobacco.

09:10.550 --> 09:12.943
I tell her the news
and she weeps,

09:13.074 --> 09:16.556
refusing to be wed because
Morton got to her first.

09:16.686 --> 09:18.949
Ford won't marry a harlot.

09:19.036 --> 09:21.952
♪

09:22.083 --> 09:24.781
Maybe Morton
isn't as fine a match,

09:24.912 --> 09:26.914
but would you consider him
a suitor?

09:27.044 --> 09:28.872
He's dishonored my daughter.

09:31.048 --> 09:33.790
Now, I told her I'd see him
dead at her feet

09:33.877 --> 09:35.836
if ever he dared show
his wretched countenance

09:35.966 --> 09:38.708
within 10 miles of Brownsville.

09:38.839 --> 09:40.405
And damn my eyes

09:40.536 --> 09:42.538
if that grass-livered
spittle-snake

09:42.669 --> 09:44.801
hasn't the face
to ride right up to my door.

09:44.888 --> 09:47.761
♪

09:47.891 --> 09:50.764
You and your men
can stay the night.

09:50.894 --> 09:53.157
But when you go
on your way tomorrow,

09:53.244 --> 09:54.855
Morton won't be joining you.

09:55.029 --> 09:57.988
♪

10:07.041 --> 10:08.303
Mm.

10:12.481 --> 10:13.481
She's a bonnie wee thing.

10:14.918 --> 10:16.833
She is.

10:18.792 --> 10:21.055
To see ye with a bairn,
Sassenach.

10:23.666 --> 10:25.233
I could watch ye hold her
all day.

10:29.063 --> 10:31.805
I hope we're not too far
from Brownsville.

10:31.935 --> 10:33.545
She won't do well
on goat's milk alone.

10:35.547 --> 10:36.787
We should be there before dusk.

10:37.898 --> 10:39.682
Dinna fash.

10:39.813 --> 10:41.413
We'll find someone
to nurse wee "Bonnie."

10:43.730 --> 10:45.427
And what then?

10:46.602 --> 10:48.604
Do we bring a newborn
all the way to Hillsborough?

10:49.170 --> 10:50.824
I'm not sure it's the best way

10:50.954 --> 10:53.522
to put the fear of God
into the Regulators,

10:53.653 --> 10:56.220
unless they're afraid
of a few dirty diapers.

10:56.351 --> 10:57.831
Hmm.

10:57.961 --> 11:00.398
The surest way to send
any man scurrying for cover.

11:00.529 --> 11:02.052
Hmm.

11:20.984 --> 11:22.682
Some of the men,

11:22.812 --> 11:24.771
Robertson, Morrison,

11:24.901 --> 11:28.731
and a few others...
are gone.

11:28.862 --> 11:30.382
Gone?
What do you mean gone?
Gone where?

11:31.908 --> 11:33.214
They don't respect what you did.

11:33.344 --> 11:34.563
What I did?

11:36.739 --> 11:39.394
- Well, I had to do something.
- I know, and I agree.

11:41.004 --> 11:44.007
But they didn't.
I'm-I'm-I'm sorry.
I tried.

11:44.138 --> 11:45.487
Ah, Christ.

12:01.459 --> 12:03.287
Sounds like Roger's
won them over.

12:03.461 --> 12:05.855
♪ Where ha' ye been
a' the day ♪

12:06.029 --> 12:08.553
♪ Bonnie laddie,
Hielan' laddie ♪

12:08.640 --> 12:11.208
♪ Saw ye him that' far awa' ♪

12:11.295 --> 12:13.776
♪ Bonnie laddie,
Hielan' laddie ♪

12:13.950 --> 12:16.518
♪ On his head a bonnet blue ♪

12:16.692 --> 12:19.129
♪ Bonnie laddie,
Hielan' laddie ♪

12:19.216 --> 12:21.741
♪ Tartan plaid
and Hielan' trews ♪

12:21.915 --> 12:25.832
♪ Bonnie laddie,
Hielan' laddie ♪

12:26.006 --> 12:28.356
♪ When he drew
his gude braid-sword ♪

12:28.530 --> 12:30.967
♪ Bonnie laddie,
Hielan' laddie ♪

12:31.141 --> 12:33.143
♪ Then he gave
his royal word ♪

12:33.274 --> 12:34.710
Josiah.

12:34.884 --> 12:36.668
♪ Hielan' laddie ♪

12:36.756 --> 12:39.019
I have secured you
and your brother's
indenture papers.

12:39.149 --> 12:41.064
Ye willna see
Mr. Beardsley again.

12:41.238 --> 12:43.110
♪ Wi' his friends
wad live or dee ♪

12:43.240 --> 12:44.240
What about the mistress?

12:45.634 --> 12:48.550
Well, she's gone for good.

12:48.680 --> 12:50.639
She left her baby with us.

12:50.770 --> 12:51.921
I didn't know
she was with child.

12:51.945 --> 12:53.685
♪

12:53.816 --> 12:56.384
Kezzie told me the mistress
may have lain with...

12:56.514 --> 12:58.647
well, there's a man,
a former slave.

12:58.778 --> 13:00.954
He came looking for work
once or twice.

13:01.084 --> 13:04.784
Then all of us...

13:04.871 --> 13:05.959
we're all free?

13:07.308 --> 13:08.962
Aye, lad.

13:10.267 --> 13:11.791
♪

13:11.921 --> 13:13.203
Does that mean we can
ride on to Hillsborough

13:13.227 --> 13:14.402
with your militia?

13:14.532 --> 13:15.532
How old are ye?

13:15.577 --> 13:17.492
♪

13:17.622 --> 13:18.928
Ye canna be more than 14.

13:19.015 --> 13:20.800
I must be older than that.

13:20.930 --> 13:23.759
I'm telling ye, ye're 14,
too young to fight.

13:23.933 --> 13:25.195
♪

13:25.282 --> 13:26.893
Aye, Colonel.

13:27.023 --> 13:29.547
Ye've fought hard
to earn your freedom.

13:29.678 --> 13:32.986
I willna let ye lose it
in death on the battlefield.

13:33.116 --> 13:35.162
Go home.

13:35.292 --> 13:38.208
Hunt.
Provide for the Ridge.

13:38.382 --> 13:39.949
♪ Charlie yet shall mount
the throne ♪

13:40.123 --> 13:42.386
♪ Bonnie laddie,
Hielan' laddie ♪

13:42.560 --> 13:45.259
♪ Weel, ye ken it is his own ♪

13:45.346 --> 13:48.697
♪ Bonnie laddie,
Hielan' laddie ♪

13:54.485 --> 13:57.575
♪

14:03.668 --> 14:05.583
♪

14:05.714 --> 14:07.150
Fergus.

14:07.324 --> 14:10.371
♪

14:10.501 --> 14:12.721
Is that our whisky?

14:12.852 --> 14:15.202
Oui, milord.
There was a small difficulty.

14:15.332 --> 14:18.161
Uh, before you explain,
I also have a small difficulty.

14:18.248 --> 14:19.946
Congratulations.

14:20.076 --> 14:21.686
You work fast, milord.

14:21.817 --> 14:23.645
Uh, the baby
needs milk urgently.

14:23.732 --> 14:25.172
Are there any
nursing mothers around?

14:25.299 --> 14:27.127
Mothers, no.

14:27.257 --> 14:29.377
But the lady of the house
will surely be able to help.

14:29.433 --> 14:31.740
♪

14:31.871 --> 14:34.395
Hi, I'm sorry to bother you.

14:37.267 --> 14:40.009
♪

14:48.713 --> 14:50.672
This is Mistress Claire Fraser
of Fraser's Ridge,

14:50.802 --> 14:52.543
colonel's wife.

14:52.674 --> 14:54.894
My daughter-in-law Lucinda
just gave birth.

14:55.024 --> 14:56.175
She'll have the milk
for the babe.

14:56.199 --> 14:58.245
Oh, I'm so sorry to intrude.

14:58.332 --> 15:00.116
This little one was born
a few days ago.

15:00.203 --> 15:01.726
She's not mine.

15:01.857 --> 15:03.356
I fed her goat's milk
on the road here, but...

15:03.380 --> 15:04.540
She needs to be fed properly.

15:05.905 --> 15:08.081
Okay.

15:09.473 --> 15:11.214
Oh.

15:13.042 --> 15:14.478
Such a strong and healthy babe.

15:14.609 --> 15:15.697
Hmm.

15:15.827 --> 15:16.872
Beautiful.

15:18.134 --> 15:19.179
A girl?

15:19.309 --> 15:20.528
Yes.

15:22.747 --> 15:23.747
Does she have a name?

15:23.792 --> 15:25.881
No.

15:26.012 --> 15:28.207
She lost both her parents
before they could christen her.

15:28.231 --> 15:29.624
Is she a slave's babe?

15:30.842 --> 15:32.670
Not quite.

15:32.801 --> 15:33.921
How'd you come by her, then?

15:38.459 --> 15:40.809
What's this "difficulty"
Fergus told me about?

15:40.896 --> 15:43.725
Wee bit of a misunderstanding
on our arrival.

15:43.855 --> 15:46.206
And ye cleared it up
with our whisky?

15:46.293 --> 15:48.121
When in Rome,
do as the Romans do.

15:48.295 --> 15:50.514
♪

15:50.645 --> 15:51.951
When I was a professor
at Oxford,

15:52.081 --> 15:54.997
I loved telling my students
about words and phrases,

15:55.128 --> 15:56.433
their origins, their meanings.

15:56.564 --> 15:57.671
Do you know where the expression

15:57.695 --> 15:59.871
"Dutch courage" comes from?

16:00.002 --> 16:01.569
I'm sure ye're about to tell me.

16:01.699 --> 16:03.049
What's it got to do wi' Rome?

16:03.179 --> 16:05.138
Some say it dates back
a century ago

16:05.268 --> 16:06.898
to when English troops
would drink to calm themselves

16:06.922 --> 16:08.880
before heading into battle.

16:09.011 --> 16:10.317
Others say the English witnessed

16:10.447 --> 16:12.319
the incredible courage
gin gave the Dutch.

16:12.449 --> 16:15.235
A number of times in history,
an advance of soldiers

16:15.365 --> 16:19.108
were stopped by an exchange
of alcohol or goods.

16:19.239 --> 16:20.849
Take the First World War,
for example.

16:20.980 --> 16:22.958
There was a daily rum ration
on the western front...

16:22.982 --> 16:24.244
Where are Morrison and Scott?

16:25.941 --> 16:27.377
Piss drunk already?

16:27.508 --> 16:28.988
No.

16:29.118 --> 16:30.772
They left...

16:30.902 --> 16:32.513
and, with them, three more.

16:32.600 --> 16:34.602
Left?
Why?

16:34.776 --> 16:37.474
♪

16:42.001 --> 16:45.482
♪

16:46.483 --> 16:49.138
Ye allowed Lionel Brown
to do this to one of yer men?

16:50.139 --> 16:51.421
They wanted to blow Morton
to smithereens.

16:51.445 --> 16:53.186
I had to...

16:53.316 --> 16:55.884
I had to agree to some kind
of temporary confinement.

16:55.971 --> 16:58.191
And what were you gonna do
once the whisky ran out?

16:58.321 --> 17:01.281
I was hoping you would arrive
before that happened,
and you did.

17:01.368 --> 17:04.023
♪

17:10.812 --> 17:13.510
I avoided confrontation.
I kept the peace.

17:13.641 --> 17:17.036
Do ye ken the meaning
of the word "captain,"
Professor MacKenzie?

17:17.166 --> 17:19.038
Is that one ye can
explain to me?

17:19.125 --> 17:21.997
Yer men left because
ye betrayed their trust.

17:22.128 --> 17:24.217
Those who remain
willna have much faith left.

17:24.347 --> 17:26.088
They swore to follow us
into battle,

17:26.219 --> 17:28.003
to risk their lives.

17:28.134 --> 17:30.919
As captain, ye must honor
their loyalty above all else.

17:31.006 --> 17:32.853
What good is loyalty
if the men are hurt or worse?

17:32.877 --> 17:34.966
♪

17:35.097 --> 17:36.337
I was responsible for that too.

17:36.403 --> 17:39.449
♪

17:40.885 --> 17:44.063
♪

17:44.150 --> 17:47.805
Now, what disarray
have ye and yer cock

17:47.936 --> 17:49.242
brought upon our endeavor?

17:49.416 --> 17:52.723
♪

17:52.854 --> 17:54.899
If ye have dishonored
the Browns' daughter,

17:54.986 --> 17:56.901
ye must marry her
and put matters to rights.

17:57.032 --> 17:59.469
Ye dinna have much choice,
Isaiah.

17:59.600 --> 18:02.342
I would, Colonel, but I canna.

18:02.516 --> 18:04.474
♪

18:04.605 --> 18:08.217
Regretfully,
I already have a wife.

18:08.391 --> 18:11.220
♪

18:16.095 --> 18:18.706
I can understand
the Browns wanting to see ye
drawn and quartered.

18:21.796 --> 18:23.363
How is it ye have a wife?

18:23.493 --> 18:26.583
My marriage was arranged
between her parents and mine.

18:26.714 --> 18:31.110
Ally... Miss Brown...
She-she took a likin' to me

18:31.240 --> 18:33.199
on my travels
through Brownsville.

18:33.329 --> 18:35.418
And I took a likin' to her.

18:35.549 --> 18:38.552
My, um... my heart
had a mind of its own.

18:38.682 --> 18:40.202
'Twas as if I had no say
in the matter.

18:42.033 --> 18:44.558
Still, ye made a vow
to yer wife and broke it.

18:46.255 --> 18:48.605
Ye swore an oath to me.

18:48.736 --> 18:50.192
How can I be certain
ye willna break it

18:50.216 --> 18:51.565
before day's end?

18:51.695 --> 18:53.132
My vow to ye was my own will.

18:53.262 --> 18:56.222
Aye, as was yer infidelity.

18:56.352 --> 18:58.025
I think we should consider
clemency for the man.

18:58.049 --> 19:01.270
After all,
"love makes fools of us all."

19:02.228 --> 19:05.013
Ye must leave.
Dinna show yer face here again.

19:05.144 --> 19:06.406
I meant no trouble for ye.

19:06.536 --> 19:08.376
As yer colonel, I'll take care
of your trouble.

19:10.453 --> 19:11.976
What's stopping ye?

19:12.107 --> 19:13.326
I'll never see Ally again.

19:14.892 --> 19:16.590
Go.

19:16.720 --> 19:17.960
It'll be better for both of ye.

19:18.069 --> 19:20.898
♪

19:29.690 --> 19:32.083
They'll come looking for him.

19:32.214 --> 19:33.781
And they willna find him.

19:33.955 --> 19:37.524
♪

19:38.829 --> 19:42.920
So Mistress Beardsley
disappeared and left us
with the child.

19:43.007 --> 19:44.792
When we went outside,

19:44.922 --> 19:46.794
we found
Mr. Beardsley's grave.

19:46.924 --> 19:49.057
She probably killed the bastard.

19:49.188 --> 19:51.494
Ma, you always think
the worst of people.

19:51.581 --> 19:53.279
I'm just saying, is all.

19:53.366 --> 19:55.194
Beardsleys were strange,

19:55.324 --> 19:57.021
came through here once
on their way home,

19:57.152 --> 19:58.806
didn't say a word.

20:01.112 --> 20:02.766
So the babe's dark.

20:02.897 --> 20:04.681
Aaron Beardsley
wasn't the father.

20:04.812 --> 20:06.857
No.

20:06.988 --> 20:08.729
Fanny Beardsley may be strange,

20:08.859 --> 20:12.080
but she isn't the first woman
to find herself in...

20:12.167 --> 20:14.604
an unsuitable situation,

20:14.735 --> 20:16.476
and she certainly
won't be the last.

20:20.610 --> 20:22.960
Oh, I'm so sorry.

20:23.091 --> 20:24.832
Oh, don't worry.

20:24.962 --> 20:26.964
Funny you should spill cider
on it, in fact.

20:27.095 --> 20:29.445
I don't know who these
physicians think they are
these days,

20:29.532 --> 20:31.447
writing to the broadsheets
with their "wisdom."

20:31.578 --> 20:35.016
It speaks of means to prevent
becoming with child.

20:35.146 --> 20:37.192
"A woman is most fertile
between"...

20:37.279 --> 20:40.282
Alicia, it is improper to speak
of such things in company.

20:43.416 --> 20:45.287
May I see that?

20:45.374 --> 20:48.203
Trust you to draw her attention
to that vulgar nonsense.

20:49.900 --> 20:52.381
Have you no compassion
for your cousin?

20:52.468 --> 20:56.255
There now, my little lady.

20:56.385 --> 20:58.082
You'll do well here with us.

20:58.213 --> 21:00.128
The babe's a beauty.

21:00.259 --> 21:02.696
We're not here to judge her
for her parents' sins.

21:02.826 --> 21:06.874
If you like, Mistress Fraser,
I'll take the babe tonight.

21:07.004 --> 21:10.660
It won't do you much good
to be woken up
by a screaming child

21:10.747 --> 21:13.054
when I can feed her here.

21:13.184 --> 21:15.544
Won't your husband mind
you having to feed
two hungry mouths?

21:16.884 --> 21:17.885
No bother at all.

21:18.059 --> 21:19.713
♪

21:19.843 --> 21:21.410
My husband is a fair man.

21:21.541 --> 21:23.282
A fair man who fired
at my Isaiah.

21:23.412 --> 21:25.893
Aye, he did,
and very fairly at that.

21:26.023 --> 21:28.896
No one to blame but yourself.

21:28.983 --> 21:31.725
If your poor mother could see
how lowly you'd fallen.

21:31.812 --> 21:34.467
♪

21:34.597 --> 21:36.904
Would it be all right
if I, uh, take this?

21:37.078 --> 21:40.299
♪

21:40.429 --> 21:44.215
I, um... I could use it
to, um, light a fire.

21:44.346 --> 21:46.348
That's all it's good for.

21:46.435 --> 21:48.176
♪

21:48.307 --> 21:49.873
Thank you for your kindness.

21:51.875 --> 21:54.225
♪ There was twa
recruitin' sergeants ♪

21:54.400 --> 21:56.402
♪ Came frae the Black Watch ♪

21:56.576 --> 21:59.709
♪ Through markets and fairs,
some recruits for to catch ♪

21:59.840 --> 22:01.972
Well, you've only lost
a few men.

22:02.059 --> 22:04.192
Men are what I need
for this show of force.

22:05.976 --> 22:08.022
And what should Roger have done?

22:08.152 --> 22:09.937
Well, he had command
of near two dozen men.

22:10.067 --> 22:13.462
One word from him,
and the Browns
would have been outnumbered.

22:13.549 --> 22:15.830
Instead he had them stand down
and gave up one of his own.

22:17.248 --> 22:18.989
Actions have consequences,
Sassenach.

22:19.120 --> 22:21.296
Yes, I know they do,

22:21.427 --> 22:22.665
but everyone can make a mistake.

22:22.689 --> 22:25.126
♪

22:25.256 --> 22:29.260
Here, look at this.

22:29.348 --> 22:33.308
♪ Horses was to fleg
and yer owsen was to rin ♪

22:33.395 --> 22:34.614
Who's Dr. Rawlings?

22:34.744 --> 22:36.050
Me.

22:37.312 --> 22:39.270
You?

22:39.401 --> 22:42.056
Beauchamp, Randall,
Fraser, now Rawlings?

22:42.186 --> 22:43.866
Ye have another husband
I should ken about?

22:43.971 --> 22:45.842
It's a pseudonym.

22:45.973 --> 22:48.758
That was the doctor's name
of the medical equipment
you gave me.

22:48.889 --> 22:50.049
You wrote to the broadsheets?

22:50.151 --> 22:51.631
No.

22:51.761 --> 22:54.982
No, I wrote out some
medical advice for the Ridge

22:55.069 --> 22:57.158
to dispel certain superstitions.

22:57.288 --> 22:58.899
Never intended for it
to go any further.

22:58.986 --> 23:01.336
♪

23:01.467 --> 23:03.836
Who would have submitted
it to the printer
without me knowing?

23:03.860 --> 23:06.254
♪ That greedy ol' farmer
thinks you never will tire ♪

23:06.385 --> 23:08.474
Matured in oak casks,
you say, huh?

23:08.561 --> 23:11.564
Aye, the Scottish way.

23:11.694 --> 23:15.089
Of course, it doesn't compare
to the wine from Champagne en France.

23:15.219 --> 23:18.092
That's a damsel's drink
if ever I heard of one.

23:22.357 --> 23:26.230
Fergus... that advertisement

23:26.361 --> 23:28.145
ye took to the printer,

23:28.276 --> 23:30.409
ye remember the paper
ye wrote on?

23:30.539 --> 23:31.908
Did it have writing
on the other side?

23:31.932 --> 23:32.933
There was.

23:34.151 --> 23:35.718
Why?

23:35.849 --> 23:38.155
Ah, printer must have
decided to use it,

23:38.286 --> 23:41.898
a very respectable name,
after all, "Dr. Rawlings."

23:42.029 --> 23:43.944
Do you think it will
cause us any trouble?

23:44.074 --> 23:46.033
I mean, will anyone
associate it with Fergus

23:46.163 --> 23:47.556
or the Ridge?

23:47.687 --> 23:50.603
Not unless someone
tries to find the author,

23:50.733 --> 23:54.084
invite him to speak
on how "bloodletting
is a harmful practice."

23:54.215 --> 23:55.869
He's gone. He's gone!

23:55.956 --> 23:57.218
He's gone!

23:59.046 --> 24:01.744
Morton's gone!
He's gone!

24:01.875 --> 24:03.833
Morton's gone.

24:03.964 --> 24:06.662
What are you telling me, boy?
Was no one guarding him?

24:06.793 --> 24:07.924
No, they were drinking.

24:08.055 --> 24:10.013
Find him, and when you do,

24:10.144 --> 24:11.624
don't wait for me.

24:11.754 --> 24:14.278
No, Morton is a militiaman
under my protection.

24:14.409 --> 24:16.498
Well, we're as protective
as you, Colonel,

24:16.585 --> 24:18.848
only I protect my own.

24:18.979 --> 24:20.894
Ho! Ho there!

24:21.068 --> 24:23.897
♪

24:25.464 --> 24:27.727
What in God's name's going on?

24:27.814 --> 24:29.555
I had Isaiah Morton.

24:29.685 --> 24:32.166
He was here,
can't have gone far.

24:32.296 --> 24:34.255
Did you have any luck
with Elijah Ford?

24:34.429 --> 24:36.300
♪

24:36.431 --> 24:38.433
He could not be persuaded.

24:39.129 --> 24:41.175
Well, we can still catch Morton,

24:41.305 --> 24:43.177
if the militia will
step out of my way.

24:43.264 --> 24:45.571
I'm Colonel James Fraser.

24:45.701 --> 24:47.573
Any harm done to Morton

24:47.703 --> 24:50.140
will be considered an act of
aggression against my militia,

24:50.271 --> 24:52.403
formed by His Excellency, Governor Tryon.

24:52.534 --> 24:55.450
I'll have no choice
but to consider ye

24:55.581 --> 24:57.800
traitors to the crown,

24:57.887 --> 25:00.047
no better than the Regulators
we were sent to disperse.

25:01.369 --> 25:03.545
Who are you calling a traitor?

25:03.676 --> 25:05.112
Stop, brother.

25:06.853 --> 25:08.332
You sound foolish.

25:10.160 --> 25:13.512
And a drunken fool at that.

25:13.599 --> 25:15.601
I want Morton as much as you do.

25:17.516 --> 25:19.474
So I am gonna talk
to Colonel Fraser...

25:19.648 --> 25:22.521
♪

25:24.479 --> 25:26.655
Come to an understanding.

25:26.829 --> 25:29.484
♪

25:32.618 --> 25:33.662
Is that clear?

25:33.836 --> 25:36.578
♪

25:40.843 --> 25:43.759
You keep strange company,
Colonel Fraser.

25:44.847 --> 25:46.501
Isaiah Morton...

25:48.677 --> 25:50.505
Not of the God-fearing kind.

25:53.247 --> 25:55.597
Little I can do
about a man's character.

25:58.513 --> 26:00.193
There's enough sin
and lawlessness each day

26:00.254 --> 26:02.343
without counting
those Regulators

26:02.473 --> 26:04.563
causing disorder
on an already
crumbling society.

26:07.609 --> 26:09.449
And we don't want no trouble
with the governor.

26:12.179 --> 26:14.355
So if you have come recruiting,

26:14.485 --> 26:16.226
you could not have found
any better men

26:16.313 --> 26:18.054
in all the Carolinas.

26:18.185 --> 26:21.710
We'll ride to Hillsborough
with you,

26:21.841 --> 26:23.201
but they'll all
be answering to me.

26:24.713 --> 26:27.542
♪

26:30.414 --> 26:34.157
Long as we're in agreement
ye will answer to me.

26:34.331 --> 26:36.595
♪

26:48.998 --> 26:50.434
You'll stay the night with us?

26:52.436 --> 26:53.612
If it's no trouble.

26:53.742 --> 26:55.439
What sort of man would I be

26:55.526 --> 26:57.790
if I allowed a lady to sleep
out with the militia

26:57.920 --> 26:59.182
on a cold, dark night?

26:59.356 --> 27:02.098
♪

27:45.446 --> 27:48.362
♪

28:08.382 --> 28:09.731
Jemmy.

28:13.387 --> 28:14.387
Jemmy?

28:15.824 --> 28:17.652
Where's Jemmy?
Where'd he go?

28:17.783 --> 28:19.088
Ball.

28:19.219 --> 28:21.961
Germain, look at me.
Did you see a man?

28:22.091 --> 28:23.310
Ball.

28:23.440 --> 28:24.877
Jemmy.

28:24.964 --> 28:26.574
Jem-Jemmy?

28:28.707 --> 28:30.839
Jemmy?
Jemmy?

28:30.970 --> 28:34.060
Jemmy?
Jemmy!

28:35.975 --> 28:37.019
He-he took him.

28:37.150 --> 28:39.326
What? Who?

28:39.456 --> 28:42.285
Jemmy! Jemmy!

28:43.547 --> 28:45.612
I stepped outside for a minute,
and I-I shouldn't have.

28:45.636 --> 28:46.550
He can't have gone far,
Mistress.

28:46.637 --> 28:47.726
We'll find him.

28:47.856 --> 28:50.163
Germain, where's Jemmy?

28:50.293 --> 28:52.034
- Ball.
- Jemmy!

28:52.165 --> 28:53.253
Jemmy!

28:57.300 --> 29:01.348
Intent on finding
his precious trinket,
that's all.

29:01.522 --> 29:04.351
♪

29:07.746 --> 29:10.574
There we are, safe and sound.

29:10.661 --> 29:12.315
Off to bed, everyone.

29:15.623 --> 29:16.711
I know.

29:19.540 --> 29:21.194
Meet me in the kitchen.

29:21.324 --> 29:24.110
I ken an honest cure
for waking nightmares.

29:32.596 --> 29:34.381
Okay, bud.

29:34.511 --> 29:37.079
Connor Brown.

29:37.210 --> 29:38.907
Hiram Brown.

29:39.081 --> 29:41.649
♪

29:41.780 --> 29:43.694
Phineas Brown.

29:43.869 --> 29:46.785
♪

29:46.915 --> 29:48.569
Abner Brown.

29:48.743 --> 29:51.572
♪

29:56.142 --> 29:59.014
♪

30:13.072 --> 30:14.682
Will this do for you
and your husband?

30:14.813 --> 30:18.033
It's perfect.
Thank you.

30:18.164 --> 30:20.209
I hope you don't think
we're a family of ill repute

30:20.296 --> 30:22.168
with all that's happened.

30:23.299 --> 30:25.419
Perhaps God sent you
to bring us the babe
for a reason.

30:27.129 --> 30:29.523
If you're looking
for a home for her,

30:29.653 --> 30:31.525
we would care for her
as if she's ours.

30:33.135 --> 30:34.223
That's very kind.

30:36.095 --> 30:39.576
You see, Lucinda's own
was born too little.

30:41.448 --> 30:42.448
She passed.

30:44.451 --> 30:46.148
I'm so sorry.

30:50.152 --> 30:51.850
Alicia will help you
with the bedding.

30:54.287 --> 30:55.647
Come and join us
when you're ready.

31:01.207 --> 31:04.123
♪

31:13.132 --> 31:16.135
Mistress Fraser...

31:16.265 --> 31:17.919
I heard.

31:18.050 --> 31:19.790
Is Isaiah truly gone?

31:21.183 --> 31:23.533
Better he stay gone,

31:23.664 --> 31:26.406
considering your father's
feelings about him.

31:26.536 --> 31:29.583
I know... but...

31:29.670 --> 31:31.541
But what?

31:31.628 --> 31:34.022
He's my first thought
in the morning

31:34.153 --> 31:35.589
and my last thought at night.

31:37.721 --> 31:39.898
He never spoke of marriage,

31:39.985 --> 31:42.988
but I wouldn't have lain
with him if I thought...

31:46.252 --> 31:49.124
Will you ask your husband,
if he sees Isaiah again,

31:49.211 --> 31:51.126
to tell him
that I'll follow him wherever?

31:51.213 --> 31:52.475
I'll do whatever I must.

31:53.607 --> 31:55.261
Alicia.

31:58.394 --> 32:00.701
Isaiah Morton...

32:00.831 --> 32:03.617
is not worth
leaving your family for.

32:03.747 --> 32:07.447
I'm sorry to have to be
the one to tell you this.

32:07.577 --> 32:09.318
He's already married.

32:12.408 --> 32:13.757
♪

32:13.888 --> 32:15.194
What do you mean?

32:15.368 --> 32:17.718
♪

32:17.848 --> 32:19.241
To whom?

32:19.415 --> 32:21.243
♪

32:21.374 --> 32:23.463
I don't know.

32:23.550 --> 32:26.379
He told my husband.

32:27.684 --> 32:29.512
Oh, he...

32:29.643 --> 32:32.559
he's also not worth your tears.

32:32.733 --> 32:35.692
♪

32:35.779 --> 32:37.303
What will I do?

32:39.696 --> 32:42.873
I'll never want anyone else,

32:42.961 --> 32:44.484
and no one else
will ever want me.

32:44.571 --> 32:47.182
♪

32:47.269 --> 32:50.142
Alicia...

32:50.272 --> 32:51.882
are you with child?

32:52.057 --> 32:54.363
♪

32:54.494 --> 32:57.540
I think so.
I don't know.

32:57.671 --> 32:59.238
Oh.

32:59.412 --> 33:01.936
♪

33:02.067 --> 33:04.721
Your family will
take care of you.

33:04.852 --> 33:07.072
No, I've disappointed them.

33:07.202 --> 33:10.553
I've ruined my... our reputation.

33:10.684 --> 33:12.251
Shh.

33:12.425 --> 33:14.557
♪

33:14.688 --> 33:16.124
I wish I was dead.

33:16.255 --> 33:17.343
No.

33:18.953 --> 33:20.824
No, that is the last thing
you should wish for.

33:23.131 --> 33:25.916
♪

33:29.790 --> 33:31.670
Ye gonna tell me
what kind of devil ye conjured?

33:36.275 --> 33:37.319
I did, didn't I?

33:39.147 --> 33:41.715
I conjured
everything up somehow.

33:41.845 --> 33:44.587
I canna help ye if I dinna ken
what ye're thinkin'.

33:49.114 --> 33:50.202
It's nothing.

33:52.334 --> 33:54.206
I mean, I-I hope it's nothing.

33:56.860 --> 34:01.213
Then we'll sit here and drink
in sacred silence.

34:05.565 --> 34:08.916
It's my own fault.
I-I shouldn't have let
Jemmy out of my sight.

34:09.047 --> 34:11.266
Nothing happened.

34:17.272 --> 34:20.406
I never told you this... but...

34:23.017 --> 34:24.149
I killed my father.

34:27.761 --> 34:32.548
He beat us... hand, belt, pot...

34:32.679 --> 34:35.551
whatever was close,
whenever he felt the urge,

34:35.682 --> 34:37.814
which was often.

34:37.901 --> 34:41.949
He once broke my lip.
Couldna speak for a month.

34:42.080 --> 34:44.517
I prayed every night
that he would stop.

34:46.780 --> 34:48.042
Wished him dead.

34:49.826 --> 34:52.655
And then one day...

34:52.786 --> 34:54.353
he was arrested as a Jacobite.

34:57.051 --> 35:01.316
Though I prayed every night
for God to take him.

35:01.447 --> 35:04.972
I let my mind be consumed

35:05.059 --> 35:07.539
by thoughts
of all the terrible things
that could happen to him.

35:10.586 --> 35:12.284
♪

35:12.414 --> 35:14.895
He died in prison.

35:15.025 --> 35:16.157
I killed him.

35:17.550 --> 35:19.334
You didn't kill him.

35:21.075 --> 35:23.904
♪

35:25.427 --> 35:28.169
You see, thinking,

35:28.300 --> 35:30.911
no matter how hard or long,

35:31.041 --> 35:32.565
doesna make something come true.

35:32.739 --> 35:35.524
♪

35:39.572 --> 35:41.965
Or else I'd be the queen
of some castle

35:42.096 --> 35:43.793
filled with jewels
and fine wines.

35:45.926 --> 35:48.842
♪

35:52.933 --> 35:54.064
Thank you.

36:01.159 --> 36:03.291
♪

36:03.378 --> 36:04.921
Our men are
putting up the tents
for the night, Mistress,

36:04.945 --> 36:05.946
up the road.

36:06.076 --> 36:07.469
They need a hand.

36:07.600 --> 36:08.688
Good.

36:10.907 --> 36:12.648
Wait, come here.

36:12.822 --> 36:15.782
♪

36:22.223 --> 36:24.878
Open your mouth.

36:25.008 --> 36:26.445
Stick out your tongue.

36:26.575 --> 36:27.446
Ah.

36:27.533 --> 36:30.318
♪

36:30.405 --> 36:32.973
Jesus H. Roosevelt Christ.

36:33.103 --> 36:35.628
Must you two be alike
in every way?

36:35.758 --> 36:37.412
Is all well with him?

36:38.848 --> 36:42.243
Does your throat hurt
from time to time
like your brother's?

36:43.723 --> 36:45.203
Aye, comes and goes.

36:45.377 --> 36:47.596
♪

36:47.727 --> 36:49.729
Well, there's nothing
I can do it about it tonight.

36:49.859 --> 36:53.385
But make sure to drink plenty...
Water or ale...

36:53.515 --> 36:55.996
And pitch your tent
at a fair distance.

36:56.126 --> 36:57.476
Aye, Mistress.

36:57.563 --> 37:00.000
♪

37:05.701 --> 37:07.529
It's about 20 miles.

37:07.660 --> 37:09.401
It's about two...

37:09.575 --> 37:12.752
♪

37:13.405 --> 37:15.450
- What is it, Sassenach?
- Kezzie.

37:15.537 --> 37:18.366
His tonsils are as infected
as his brother's.

37:18.497 --> 37:20.217
Must have contracted it
from Josiah somehow.

37:21.543 --> 37:23.241
His fever's very high.

37:23.371 --> 37:25.068
Josiah's strong enough
to wait for surgery,

37:25.199 --> 37:26.319
but I don't think Kezzie is.

37:27.593 --> 37:29.159
Can ye perform it here?

37:30.204 --> 37:32.511
I need penicillin
for this kind of surgery.

37:34.077 --> 37:35.165
And ye don't have that yet?

37:36.906 --> 37:38.908
No, I feel I was close

37:39.039 --> 37:40.190
to finding the right strain
before we left.

37:40.214 --> 37:42.738
♪

37:42.825 --> 37:44.566
Then ye must return
with them to the Ridge.

37:44.653 --> 37:47.221
Josiah's no use to me here.

37:47.352 --> 37:48.744
The Ridge needs a hunter, and...

37:48.831 --> 37:51.573
Keziah's no good to anyone dead.

37:51.704 --> 37:53.144
What if you encounter
the Regulators?

37:54.707 --> 37:56.404
Won't you need me?

37:56.535 --> 37:58.319
Well, ye said ye didna ken
of any battles.

37:59.625 --> 38:03.150
No, nor did Brianna.

38:05.979 --> 38:07.328
I don't want to leave you
so soon.

38:07.415 --> 38:09.983
♪

38:10.113 --> 38:11.941
We didna spend a day in hell

38:12.072 --> 38:14.814
to secure the safety
of those lads to...

38:14.944 --> 38:16.468
see them suffer now.

38:17.556 --> 38:19.035
Heal them both...

38:19.209 --> 38:21.995
♪

38:24.214 --> 38:25.303
And return to me.

38:26.913 --> 38:27.914
Roger Mac.

38:28.088 --> 38:30.656
♪

38:30.786 --> 38:32.571
Colonel.

38:32.745 --> 38:35.835
♪

38:35.965 --> 38:39.142
Come dawn,
ye will escort Claire home.

38:39.273 --> 38:41.754
What?
Why?

38:43.408 --> 38:46.367
I need to take the twins
back to my surgery.

38:48.238 --> 38:51.154
What about the militia
and Hillsborough?

38:51.241 --> 38:53.983
I made ye a captain
without time to prepare ye

38:54.114 --> 38:55.942
or teach you
what the word meant.

38:56.029 --> 38:58.553
From the old French capitaine
via the Latin...

38:58.684 --> 38:59.946
Lead my wife home.

39:04.907 --> 39:06.648
Don't worry.

39:06.779 --> 39:08.459
We'll be back with them
before you know it.

39:08.563 --> 39:10.086
It's not that that concerns me.

39:12.045 --> 39:13.829
He doesna have any faith in me.

39:15.048 --> 39:17.485
He just entrusted you
with the one thing
he loves most.

39:19.792 --> 39:20.967
Aye.

39:24.100 --> 39:26.886
♪

39:36.939 --> 39:39.681
♪

39:48.298 --> 39:51.127
♪

40:04.053 --> 40:06.969
♪

40:09.972 --> 40:13.019
Go. Go and dance.

40:15.151 --> 40:16.631
I hope my mother-in-law told you

40:16.762 --> 40:18.130
that if you're looking
for a good home...

40:18.154 --> 40:19.982
We don't mind keeping her.

40:20.592 --> 40:22.507
Are you quite sure?

40:22.594 --> 40:26.685
It's not her fault
how she came into this world,

40:26.772 --> 40:29.035
and we have plenty of room
to spare now.

40:29.165 --> 40:31.603
She wouldn't lack for anything.

40:31.733 --> 40:33.213
If you'd allow it.

40:33.343 --> 40:35.389
Well, I'd have to speak
with my husband.

40:35.520 --> 40:37.086
Of course.

40:37.260 --> 40:40.176
♪

40:56.889 --> 40:58.891
Hey!

41:00.501 --> 41:01.781
Here, would you like
to take her?

41:21.479 --> 41:23.219
♪

41:25.308 --> 41:28.355
♪

41:28.486 --> 41:29.486
Oh.

41:29.574 --> 41:30.662
Oh.

41:33.099 --> 41:35.231
Go on, Mac Dubh.

42:06.698 --> 42:09.788
♪

42:13.052 --> 42:15.968
♪

42:27.719 --> 42:30.373
♪

42:30.504 --> 42:32.462
Mac Dubh! Go on, Mac Dubh!

42:44.518 --> 42:46.259
Didn't know you could dance
like that.

42:54.615 --> 42:56.661
Where are you taking me?

42:56.791 --> 42:59.620
Heh. Away from prying eyes.

43:00.926 --> 43:02.580
Well, I should warn you,

43:02.710 --> 43:05.017
my husband's as jealous
as he is handsome.

43:05.147 --> 43:06.322
Huh.

43:06.453 --> 43:08.934
And you should know I can...

43:09.064 --> 43:10.979
knock you off your feet, sir.

43:12.328 --> 43:13.852
You can't even walk

43:13.939 --> 43:14.983
in a straight line.

43:17.029 --> 43:18.857
Can you recite the alphabet
backwards?

43:18.987 --> 43:22.600
I expect so.
English or Greek?

43:22.730 --> 43:25.428
Well, never mind.

43:25.559 --> 43:27.300
If you can recite
either of those forwards,

43:27.430 --> 43:29.084
then you're in
a better condition than I.

43:29.215 --> 43:30.259
Mm.

43:30.390 --> 43:31.826
Hmm.

43:31.913 --> 43:34.873
Ah.

43:37.397 --> 43:40.400
There's a...

43:40.487 --> 43:42.358
a question I wanna ask ye.

43:42.489 --> 43:43.969
What?

43:46.493 --> 43:48.016
Do ye want wee Bonnie?

43:49.714 --> 43:50.714
Do ye wanna keep her?

43:53.587 --> 43:54.980
We have a big house.

43:56.851 --> 43:58.418
I've seen ye with her,
Sassenach.

44:00.420 --> 44:03.075
I've seen how you-you would
ha' looked with Bree.

44:03.249 --> 44:06.469
♪

44:06.600 --> 44:09.081
And I thought maybe this
might be the last chance

44:09.211 --> 44:10.778
for us to raise
a bairn together.

44:10.952 --> 44:13.259
♪

44:14.521 --> 44:16.262
What would you think
if she stayed?

44:17.480 --> 44:20.179
Here... in Brownsville?

44:20.266 --> 44:22.137
♪

44:22.268 --> 44:23.617
It's been suggested.

44:23.791 --> 44:26.315
♪

44:26.446 --> 44:29.623
Lucinda's taken a liking to her.

44:29.710 --> 44:33.018
I think she needs
our wee Bonnie
more than anyone.

44:34.802 --> 44:37.196
She'd be in good hands.

44:37.326 --> 44:41.635
Bonnie comes with the deed
to the Beardsley property.

44:43.332 --> 44:46.205
After the trouble with Alicia,

44:46.335 --> 44:48.255
it'd be a welcome addition
to the Browns' estate.

44:50.209 --> 44:52.690
I have no life but you, Claire.

44:54.561 --> 44:56.998
But if ye wanted another child,

44:57.129 --> 45:00.523
I thought that perhaps
I might give ye one,

45:00.654 --> 45:02.525
one that ye wouldn't have
to suffer carrying.

45:05.615 --> 45:07.748
♪

45:07.835 --> 45:10.925
Please know...

45:11.056 --> 45:14.712
that if it's at all possible...

45:14.842 --> 45:18.672
I love you even more
for wanting to take the chance.

45:19.804 --> 45:23.068
I also regret that we were
never parents together.

45:23.198 --> 45:26.245
But regret...

45:26.375 --> 45:27.855
isn't reason enough.

45:28.029 --> 45:30.771
♪

45:31.685 --> 45:34.122
I love our life.

45:34.253 --> 45:36.342
I love our home together.

45:36.516 --> 45:38.344
♪

45:38.474 --> 45:40.781
Would we even be
the best home for her?

45:42.827 --> 45:45.351
Then there's our obituary.

45:45.525 --> 45:48.441
♪

45:50.312 --> 45:52.227
♪

45:52.358 --> 45:55.056
I am grateful...

45:55.187 --> 45:57.058
for every day we have.

45:57.232 --> 45:59.931
♪

46:00.061 --> 46:01.541
As am I.

46:01.715 --> 46:04.631
♪

46:11.551 --> 46:13.640
♪

46:13.771 --> 46:16.164
And Marsali and Fergus...

46:18.210 --> 46:20.536
Well, I'm sure
they will keep the Ridge
sufficiently populated,

46:20.560 --> 46:22.475
if that's what
you're worried about.

46:22.605 --> 46:26.261
Yeah, that lass is with child
every time Fergus
lays eyes upon her.

46:29.787 --> 46:31.919
And he dares to joke
about my virility.

46:32.050 --> 46:33.094
Heh.

46:36.881 --> 46:38.230
That was a gunshot.

46:38.404 --> 46:41.233
♪

46:46.194 --> 46:47.195
Here.

46:47.326 --> 46:49.763
Alicia!

46:49.937 --> 46:52.592
♪

46:52.722 --> 46:55.073
Alicia.

46:55.203 --> 46:56.726
I meant the bullet for my heart.

46:58.337 --> 47:00.905
Please, leave me
so I can try again!

47:08.477 --> 47:09.609
She's wounded.

47:11.872 --> 47:14.048
We must get her home.
Come.

47:14.179 --> 47:15.833
Shh, come.

47:15.963 --> 47:17.443
Come on.

47:17.617 --> 47:20.402
♪

47:26.060 --> 47:27.148
It's all right, darling.

47:32.414 --> 47:33.589
I'm all alone.

47:36.201 --> 47:38.551
I can't live
with what I've done.

47:38.681 --> 47:40.205
I can't live without Isaiah.

47:41.597 --> 47:45.123
You are not alone,

47:45.253 --> 47:48.082
and your baby
is worth living for.

47:52.260 --> 47:55.046
Jamie, would you find
some whisky?

47:55.176 --> 47:56.656
Settle her nerves.

48:03.750 --> 48:05.360
Morton?

48:05.491 --> 48:07.754
What in God's name
are you doing here?

48:07.841 --> 48:10.365
I couldn't leave, sir,
not without seeing Ally.

48:10.496 --> 48:11.776
Do you know
where I can find her?

48:11.801 --> 48:14.021
The lass kens
ye've a wife already.

48:14.152 --> 48:16.371
If her father sees ye,
he'll shoot ye on sight.

48:16.502 --> 48:20.375
She may stab ye to the heart,
bigamist that ye are.

48:21.463 --> 48:23.744
And if neither of them succeed,
I might do the job myself.

48:23.857 --> 48:26.512
What sort of man
gets a lass with child

48:26.599 --> 48:27.948
and no right
to give it his name?

48:28.035 --> 48:30.255
With child?

48:30.385 --> 48:32.387
Aye, she is.

48:33.867 --> 48:34.737
Now, ye'd best leave.

48:34.868 --> 48:37.349
I'm sorry, sir.

48:37.479 --> 48:40.700
I dinna wish to do you harm,
but I must see Ally.

48:40.830 --> 48:41.919
Put it down.

48:43.137 --> 48:45.096
Ye ken fine ye willna shoot me.

48:45.226 --> 48:47.011
So do I.

48:51.450 --> 48:53.060
I canna speak ill of my wife,

48:53.191 --> 48:55.106
but neither one of us was happy.

48:55.193 --> 48:57.978
We havena shared a home
nor a bed for two years now,

48:58.065 --> 49:00.502
and we've no children.

49:00.633 --> 49:04.637
Ally... uh, Miss Brown
is my heart and soul.

49:05.812 --> 49:08.293
Please, help me see her.

49:11.383 --> 49:12.688
♪

49:12.819 --> 49:14.995
Nothing in this world is worth

49:15.126 --> 49:16.954
taking your life for.

49:20.392 --> 49:23.090
♪

49:30.837 --> 49:32.143
I thought you were gone.

49:32.273 --> 49:33.318
I should be gone.

49:34.972 --> 49:36.756
Is it true?
You're with child?

49:36.930 --> 49:39.802
♪

49:41.979 --> 49:43.763
Is it true you're married?

49:44.633 --> 49:45.939
Yes.

49:47.071 --> 49:48.986
And do you love her?

49:49.987 --> 49:53.077
I love only you.

49:57.995 --> 49:59.146
I have the muster roll here,
Colonel.

49:59.170 --> 50:00.170
I just wanted to...

50:01.389 --> 50:03.261
Morton?

50:03.391 --> 50:04.784
What are you thinking
coming back?

50:06.568 --> 50:08.396
I'm a fool, as ye said,

50:08.527 --> 50:10.398
as are ye,

50:10.529 --> 50:13.053
and as is the colonel.

50:15.273 --> 50:17.468
Are ye both telling me
that if someone
told you to leave,

50:17.492 --> 50:20.408
told ye that ye'd never see
Mistress MacKenzie

50:20.539 --> 50:23.063
or Mistress Fraser again,
you'd stand for it,

50:23.194 --> 50:24.543
that ye'd obey without a fight?

50:25.805 --> 50:27.241
If either of ye would go

50:27.328 --> 50:28.634
and leave the women ye love

50:28.764 --> 50:30.810
with all yer hearts, say it now.

50:31.463 --> 50:32.638
Say ye'd go, and I'll walk

50:32.768 --> 50:34.770
out of here
without another word.

50:37.512 --> 50:40.298
♪

50:43.997 --> 50:46.260
So I was biding my time.

50:46.391 --> 50:48.828
I had to wait for nightfall
to prove it to you.

50:48.958 --> 50:50.612
Will ye have me?

50:50.699 --> 50:52.614
It may be bold and...

50:52.745 --> 50:55.095
reckless and foolish, but...

50:55.226 --> 50:57.010
how can I live without ye?

50:57.141 --> 50:59.447
Or I without you?

50:59.578 --> 51:00.666
They can't stay here.

51:00.840 --> 51:03.016
♪

51:03.147 --> 51:05.975
No, they canna.

51:09.022 --> 51:11.851
♪

51:29.651 --> 51:32.393
♪

51:52.239 --> 51:53.936
Go!

51:58.854 --> 52:01.640
♪

52:05.687 --> 52:07.820
♪

52:12.607 --> 52:15.436
♪

52:17.090 --> 52:20.354
♪

52:20.485 --> 52:22.443
- Those are our horses.
- Get after them!

52:22.617 --> 52:25.359
♪

52:38.111 --> 52:40.635
This wee devil roaming about.

52:42.333 --> 52:44.248
Must've startled the horses.

52:45.510 --> 52:47.550
They dinna take kindly
to our cloven-hooved friends.

52:48.774 --> 52:51.733
♪

52:53.692 --> 52:56.521
♪

53:04.529 --> 53:08.446
Adultery, betrayal, dishonor.

53:08.576 --> 53:12.014
Excuses could be made,
of course.

53:12.145 --> 53:14.539
I know I made my own
when I was separated
from Frank

53:14.626 --> 53:16.367
by a power I didn't understand.

53:16.454 --> 53:18.717
♪

53:18.847 --> 53:23.504
And yet, wherever you are,
you make choices:

53:23.635 --> 53:27.508
foolish ones or ones
that save yourself
or someone else.

53:29.206 --> 53:32.121
All you can hope for
is that the good

53:32.252 --> 53:34.776
will outweigh the harm
that may come of it.

53:34.950 --> 53:37.692
♪
